attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: Attempts to fulfill a single order by matching it against multiple orders from a provided list.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: This function creates a new order with the given parameters and iterates through the list of existing orders,

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: attempting to match the new order with existing orders. It handles full and partial matches according to the specified limit type:

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: - 'GTC' (Good-Til-Canceled): The order remains active until it is either fully filled or canceled.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: - 'IOC' (Immediate-Or-Cancel): The order can be partially filled immediately, and any unfilled portion is canceled.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: - 'FOK' (Fill-Or-Kill): The order must be fully filled immediately, or the entire transaction fails.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: * `amount`: [u64] - The amount of the asset to be fulfilled in the new order.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: * `order_type`: [OrderType] - The type of the order being fulfilled (e.g., buy or sell).

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: * `limit_type`: [LimitType] - The limit type for the new order: 'GTC', 'IOC', or 'FOK'.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: * `price`: [u64] - The price at which the new order is to be fulfilled.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: * `slippage`: [u64] - The maximum allowable slippage (as a percentage) for the price during the matching process.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: * `orders`: [Vec<b256>] - A vector of order IDs representing the existing orders to match against the new order.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: * [b256] - The unique identifier of the newly created order. If the order is partially matched and canceled (in the case of 'IOC'), the ID corresponds to the canceled order.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: * When order vector length is less than 1.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: * When no any orders can be fulfilled.
